// Row-aggregate identity sum(X, 0) over an n x 1 matrix, which the compiler
// rewrites to X itself: a row-wise sum touches one element per row, so the
// aggregate is the identity. X has distinct values so a wrong reduction would
// change the printed result rather than be masked.

X = [1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0];
X = reshape(X, 4, 1);

print(sum(X, 0));
